Greece legend Giorgos Karagounis has agreed a deal to become part of the Claudio Ranieri's coaching staff with the national side.

The former Fulham midfielder has been without a club since being released by the Cottagers at the end of last season.

Karagounis, 37, was part of the Greece side that won the European Championships in 2004.

